#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Create reports for inverse adding-doubling analyses.

``iadplus`` is a convenience wrapper around the ``iad`` executable. It accepts
one or more ``.rxt`` experiment files, runs ``iad`` when needed, parses the
generated ``.txt`` output, and creates a self-contained report containing the
input, output, reflection/transmission fits, derived optical properties, and a
grid plot. By default the report is a PDF; ``--notebook`` creates a Jupyter
notebook and ``--html`` writes a simple HTML report directly.

Examples:
    Generate the default PDF report for one experiment file::

        ./iadplus tests/rxt/0_sphere/basic_B.rxt

    Generate a Jupyter notebook instead::

        ./iadplus --notebook tests/rxt/0_sphere/basic_B.rxt

    Generate an HTML report::

        ./iadplus --html tests/rxt/0_sphere/basic_B.rxt

    Pass options through to ``iad`` and force the analysis to rerun::

        ./iadplus --force -M 0 -q 8 tests/rxt/0_sphere/basic_B.rxt

    Fit scattering to a power law in the default PDF report::

        ./iadplus --fit -c 0 tests/rxt/1_sphere/ville1.rxt

"""

